				<div class="talk-intro">
					<p id="tagline" class="notranslate">In this fiery and funny talk, New York Times food writer Mark Bittman weighs in on what's wrong with the way we eat now (too much meat, too few plants; too much fast food, too little home cooking), and why it's putting the entire planet at risk.</p>
											<p>
							Mark Bittman is a bestselling cookbook author, journalist and television personality. His friendly, informal approach to home cooking has shown millions that fancy execution is no substitute for flavor and soul. <a target="_blank" title="Mark Bittman's bio" href="/speakers/mark_bittman.html">Full bio »</a>						</p>
					
											<div id="attributionText">
													</div>
